Commit Message:
Add support for deserialization of the resource from JSON.

This commit adds support for deserializing a CRD from the JSON received via K8s
API. It also adds support for parsing the '.metadata' field using the
V1ObjectMeta from Kubernetes.
Add support for GH actions in tox.ini
Remove UID field since it can be confusing.
Add the ability to install a CRD to Kubernetes cluster.
Use yaml.load instead of import load directly.
Fix the ReST syntax in README
Fix the repo url in pyproject.toml
Bump version post release and add tox env for isort.
Update readme on how to deserialize the json to python resource.
Improve docstring on the base class.

Add support for watch and add example to stream watch changes.

This adds another example that streams the 'watch' API using Python as a Server
Side Event that the browser is able to display. The events are simply the
stream of events from etcd and are not doing any complicated processing other
than just rendering them in the browser page.

See examples/03-forum-webapp/ on how to run the example.
Add some minor docs in the JS code.
Update the posts if they exist instead of creating new ones.
Use a smoother transition to the new post.
Add support to save the object to cluster.
Allow customizing the namespace instead of always using default.
Add user's name to the object name. Also don't log nil errors.
Add dependency on dev version of kubecrd in examples.

Update documentation abour serialization and watch APIs.

Also, add a sync version of save() API.
Add a script to automate releases.
Autoformat code using blue and isort.
Remove versions of Python we don't need.
